                      <p>The Growling Rabbit is a neighborhood café committed to using locally sourced ingredients from local farmers to create healthy comfort food. Located in Chicago’s Rogers Park neighborhood, we try to support the “farm to table” philosophy whenever possible and when something delicious is in season, we strive to incorporate it into our wares to allow you, the patrons, to experience the season’s bounty in a unique way.</p>
                      <p>As a result of our local, seasonal ingredients, our menu also rotates seasonally taking full advantage of the harvest. The Growling Rabbit offers heartier meals in the winter like pot roast with root vegetables and lighter fares in the summer such as the lemon and herb cream cheese roasted chicken wrap. Our bake shop, Sweet Attila’s, produces fresh baked goods daily incorporating the same philosophy as the café. Why are there no blueberry muffins in January, you ask? Not only do we appreciate the “pop” of fresh, plump blueberries from our farmer friends but we also try to limit the footprints our ingredients travel and resources used as they make their way to our kitchen. The Growling Rabbit would like to show our customers that it’s possible to craft healthy meals using fresh ingredients as seasons change, and we want that idea to become a part of the community.</p>
                      <p>There are a lot of things that make us different; among them are our fabulous, multi-talented staff, our strong relationships with local artisans, and the way that we make carrot cake. We invite you to stop in, grab a bacon-cheddar scone and fresh cup of coffee and relax in front of our wall-to-wall windows; it’s a great opportunity to people watch. Or, decompress from a busy day on our patio in the summertime, as the breezes gently blow off Lake Michigan, with one of our many entrees and a glass of our refreshing Prairie Passion iced tea. If you want to know more about the local farmers we work with, you can find that information here.</p>
